    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix MBMS Session Start Request Handling in M2AP\n\n### Summary\nThe `rrc_eNB_process_M2AP_MBMS_SESSION_START_REQ` function in the eNB M2AP module was not properly utilizing the session start request parameters. Instead, it was ignoring the actual MBMS session data and reusing stale global variables, causing unexpected behavior when starting MBMS sessions.\n\nThe root cause was that the `m2ap_session_start_req_t` structure was just a dummy with no meaningful fields, and the RRC function was not validating or using the passed parameters. This led to sessions being processed with incorrect or outdated configuration data.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/COMMON/m2ap_messages_types.h`: Enhanced `m2ap_session_start_req_t` structure with proper fields for MCE-MBMS-M2AP-ID, TMGI, MBMS-Session-ID, MBMS-Service-Area, and TNL-Information based on the M2AP ASN.1 specification.\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB_M2AP.c`: Updated `rrc_eNB_process_M2AP_MBMS_SESSION_START_REQ` function to validate input parameters using AssertFatal and log session details for debugging.\n\n"
}